&lt;em&gt;Description: Show the Connections page with the main interface, including the &amp;ldquo;Add Connection&amp;rdquo; button and the search filter at the top&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Basic Concepts</title><link>https://mcp-explorer-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/getting-started/concepts/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mcp-explorer-docs.garrardkitchen.com/docs/getting-started/concepts/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-is-mcp"&gt;What is MCP? &lt;a href="#what-is-mcp" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle"&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Model Context Protocol (MCP)&lt;/strong&gt; is a standardized protocol for communication between AI applications and external services or tools. It enables:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tool Calling&lt;/strong&gt;: AI models can invoke external functions/APIs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Prompts&lt;/strong&gt;: Pre-configured message templates with dynamic arguments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Resources&lt;/strong&gt;: Access to external data sources (files, databases, APIs)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Elicitations&lt;/strong&gt;: Servers can request structured input from users&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
